## Rules

- **Single shell.** **`AppShell`** mounts once per org (or other post-login root). Use **`AppSubLayout`** for inner rails (admin, HRM) — never nest a second full shell.
- **Registry-aligned nav.** Rail slots built from capability registries (`ORG_ADMIN_CAPABILITIES`, `HRM_CAPABILITIES`, `PLATFORM_ADMIN_CAPABILITIES`) or typed data contracts. No orphaned `NAV_ITEMS` arrays.
- **L1 widgets.** Use `AppShellIconButton` / `AppShellIconLink` / `AppShellUtilityTriggerTooltip`. Do not import `#components2/ui/tooltip` via filesystem-relative paths inside `components2/app-shell/**` — use the `#components2/ui/*` alias.
- **Boring shell.** No animated chrome for novelty. Density and calm ERP posture beat marketing energy.
- **Feature two-pane layouts** (Orbit queue+detail) live **inside** `AppShellSurface` children under `lib/features/<module>/components/` — not confused with shell components.

## Forbidden

- Tenant/ERP/domain logic inside `components2/app-shell/**`.
- Deep imports into `lib/features/<module>/data/...` from shell — use `#features/<module>` or `#features/<module>/client`.
- Cross-tenant or slug-from-client assumptions — org slug comes from server guards + path builders.
- Reviving deleted repo-root `components/workbench/` or `components2/app-shell/workbench/`.
- New shell chrome inside `components/nexus/` — shell belongs in `components2/app-shell/`.
- Creating `components/dashboard/` shell directory — there is no second shell stack.

